  • k-means clustering Algorithm is simple unsupervised Algoritm

4.1 K-means¶

In [22]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

4.1.1 K-means_Cost¶

In [23]:
cost = []

for i in range(1,11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = i, init = 'k-means++', random_state = 0)
    kmeans.fit(data_values)
    cost.append(abs(kmeans.score(data_values)))
In [24]:
plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
plt.plot(range(1,11), cost)
plt.title('The K-means Clustering cost', fontsize = 20)
plt.xlabel('number of clusters', fontsize = 20)
plt.ylabel('cost', fontsize = 20)
plt.show()

versicolor_num = 0

virginica_num = 0

for real, predict in zip(real_species,kmeans_species):
    if real == 'Iris-setosa':
        setosa_num += 1
        if real == predict:
            i += 1
    elif real == 'Iris-versicolor':
        versicolor_num += 1
        if real == predict:
            j += 1
    else:
        virginica_num += 1
        if real == predict:
            k += 1
